headline: CEOs at America’s 100 largest low-wage employers are paid 632 times as much as the average worker, study finds

headline: What tariffs on Brazilian coffee mean for Starbucks & Dutch Bros
summary: After examining how President Trump's tariffs on imports from Brazil could raise coffee prices (KC=F), the Asking for a Trend team examines what increased coffee prices mean for coffee chains. Guggenheim Securities senior analyst Gregory Francfort shares his expectations for heightened coffee prices due to tariffs to hit Starbucks (SBUX) and Dutch Bros (BROS). To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.
